The File IpmbFruDevice.cpp produces the deamon "ipmb-fru-device" similar to the "fru-device" deamon.

This "ipmb-fru-device" deamon is created for handling to read/write the FRU details from  ipmb interfaces.

This deamon reads the ipmb devices list from the /usr/share/ipmbbridge/ipmb-channels.json
Then scan the ipmb devices and send ipmb commands to read the all the FRU details and create a dbus objects
under xyz.openbmc_project.Ipmb.FruDevice the dbus service.

Similarly, using ipmb commands can write the fru details.

If users want to use ipmb based fru to read the fru information,
they just need to add the ipmb channels info in the ipmb-chanels.json in the machine layers.
This ipmb-chanels.json files is used in the ipmbbridged and ipmb-fru-device deamons.
This will enable ipmb communication for the corresponding ipmi channel.
Also this will read/write the fru's info using ipmb-fru-device and create dbus-objects.

Use case :
   YosemiteV2 is multi host system. The BMC is connected with hosts with the ipmb interface.
The "ipmb-fru-device" deamon reads the ipmb channel list, scan the ipmb busses,
validate the FRU details and read/write the each host fru  details.
Finally produces the dbus-objects for the host FRU's.


Example :
1. Sample ipmb-channels.json config file :

{
  "channels": [
    {
      "type": "ipmb",
      "slave-path": "/dev/ipmb-1",
      "bmc-addr": 32,
      "remote-addr": 64,
      "devIndex": 0
    },
    {
      "type": "ipmb",
      "slave-path": "/dev/ipmb-3",
      "bmc-addr": 32,
      "remote-addr": 64,
      "devIndex": 1
    },
    {
      "type": "ipmb",
      "slave-path": "/dev/ipmb-5",
      "bmc-addr": 32,
      "remote-addr": 64,
      "devIndex": 2
    },
    {
      "type": "ipmb",
      "slave-path": "/dev/ipmb-7",
      "bmc-addr": 32,
      "remote-addr": 64,
      "devIndex": 3
    }
  ]
}


2. Sample host fru dbus-objects :

root@yosemitev2:~# busctl tree xyz.openbmc_project.Ipmb.FruDevice
  └─/xyz/openbmc_project
    └─/xyz/openbmc_project/Ipmb
      └─/xyz/openbmc_project/Ipmb/FruDevice
        ├─/xyz/openbmc_project/Ipmb/FruDevice/Twin_Lakes_Passive_MP_0
        ├─/xyz/openbmc_project/Ipmb/FruDevice/Twin_Lakes_Passive_MP_1
        ├─/xyz/openbmc_project/Ipmb/FruDevice/Twin_Lakes_Passive_MP_2
        └─/xyz/openbmc_project/Ipmb/FruDevice/Twin_Lakes_Passive_MP_3


